# CSS Stylesheet

```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  opacity: 0.3;
}
```

**Explanation:**

- `*` - Universal selector that targets all elements on the page
- `font-size: 20px;` - Sets the font size to 20 pixels
- `font-style: italic;` - Italicizes all text
- `opacity: 0.3;` - Applies 70% transparency (0.3 = 30% opaque, meaning 70% transparent)

**Note:** If you want to apply transparency only to the background instead of the entire element (which affects text readability), you could use:

```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}
```

This would preserve text visibility while making backgrounds semi-transparent.

