# C++ Version

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <cctype>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    cin.ignore(); // Ignore the newline after the integer input

    string p = "";

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        string s;
        getline(cin, s);

        string t = "";
        for (char element : s) {
            if (isupper(element) || isdigit(element)) {
                t += element;
            }
        }

        if (t.length() > 1) {
            t = "";
        }

        p += t;
    }

    cout << p << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

**Key differences from Python:**
- `int(input())` → `cin >> n`
- `input()` → `getline(cin, s)` (to read entire lines)
- `cin.ignore()` → clears the newline buffer after reading the integer
- `str.isupper()` → `isupper(element)`
- `str.isnumeric()` → `isdigit(element)`
- `len(t)` → `t.length()`
- `print()` → `cout << p << endl`

